#MEM id=nate source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/GROWTH-PRINCIPLES.md savings=7%
M|GROW|> Lo|designing a growth experiment, analyzing a funnel, prioritizing growth bets, or doing a growth rv.
M|GROW|tx|---
M|Cont|Befo|
M|Cont|tx|1. Active vt (nz or hb)
M|Cont|tx|2. `funnel_benchmarks` from memory — what are the current conversion baselines?
M|Cont|tx|3. `active_experiments` from memory — what's already running? Don't ds conflicting tests.
M|Cont|tx|4. `top_growth_levers` from memory — what's been proven to work?
M|Cont|tx|5. ka's latest data — baselines must be current before designing experiments
M|Cont|tx|Never ds an experiment w/o a confirmed baseline. Hypothesis w/o data is noise.
M|Cont|tx|---
M|AARR|Nate|
M|AARR|tx|\| Stage \| nz \| hb \|
M|AARR|tx|\|-------\|---------\|---------\|
M|AARR|tx|\| **Acquisition** \| IG followers → website visitors \| App installs \|
M|AARR|tx|\| **Activation** \| First purchase \| First sn after install \|
M|AARR|tx|\| **Retention** \| Repeat purchase (30-day) \| Weekly active us \|
M|AARR|tx|\| **rv** \| AOV, repeat cs rv \| MRR, upgrade rate \|
M|AARR|tx|\| **Referral** \| UGC, tags, word-of-mouth \| Referral invites sent \|
M|AARR|tx|Different vt = different bottlenecks. Diagnose before prescribing.
